The Standards Organisation of Nigeria (SON) has issued a red alert on the presence of substandard SUNRISE brand of electric cables in the Nigerian markets and warned consumers to avoid patronage of the product.  A statement from the office of the Director General, Osita Aboloma Esq. disclosed that a large consignment of the substandard and life-endangering SUNRISE cable which managed to find there way into the country have been apprehended and destroyed  It also warned dealers in electric cables to avoid sale of the product or risk seizure by SON officials wherever it is found as well as the prosecution of the offenders.Â SON advised the general public and in particular, users and dealers in electric cables to avoid the sale or patronage of SUNRISE brand of electric cables, the statement concluded.